There are some methods of community disinfecting that might be worthy of consideration. I am one of those in at risk senior citizens and remember as a kid the usr of crop dusting aircraft to protect our crops from insects and certain diseases. My question is: Why can’t this technology be updated and used to spray heavy concentrations of disinfectants over areas from say 8:30 pm to 1:00 am to try and reduce the virus on certain surfaces (like the spraying in malls and airports)? Why can’t thermal technology be utilized over areas to get a picture of the heat signature of the virus? Then use infrared technology in lamps in communities that already have wired shot spotters and use the heat of these lamps and infrared lighting to work in the reducing the amount of virus in the atmosphere or environment?
Thank you for reading the rambling comments from a senior citizen that comes up with crazy ideas on my daily 7 mile walks.
I am counting on you (young minds) to come up with creative technology to address methods to knock out this virus!
And may I ask as a senior citizen that we strive to be supportive of each other, instead of the critical nature often displayed on line?
One last comment to all the old crop dusters give consideration on how you can help knock out the virus.
